===Etymology===
[[Category:Greek derivations]]
From [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[Πύθων]]''' (''Python'') the name of the mythological enormous serpent at Delphi slain by Apollo, from '''[[Πυθώ]]''' (''Pytho'') the early name of Delphi, from '''[[πυθώ]]''' (''pytho'') "to rot, to decay".

===Noun===
'''python''' (''plural'' '''[[pythons]]''')

# A type of large [[constrict]]ing [[snake]].

====Translations====
